                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="DonationNote"/>
                           <locus target="#69v"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ መልእክተ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ወመልእክተ፡ ጳውሎስ፡ ዕብራውያን። ዘወሀበ፡ ፍሬ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወልዱ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ለቅዱስ፡ እስጢፋኖስ፡ በቅድመ፡ ነጋድያን፡ ፯። 
                              ራይስ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወቀሲስ፡ ዘርአ፡ ልዑል። ወቀሲስ፡ ያዕቆብ። ወቀሲስ፡ ተክለ፡ ብርሃን። ወተንሥአ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልደ፡ አቡነ፡ ኤዮስጣቴዎስ። ወዓሥራተ፡ ማርያም፡ ወልዱ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ሳሙኤል፡ 
                              ከመ፡ ትኩኖ፡ መድኃኒ<supplied reason="omitted">ተ</supplied>፡ ነፍሱ። ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘተአገላ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ይኩን፡ በአፉሆሙ፡ ለጴጥሮስ፡ ወለጳውሎስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ወአሜን።
                           </q>
                           <note>The note states that <persName ref="PRS11225FereMi">Fǝre Mikāʾel</persName>, <persName ref="PRS11208HouseTakla">spiritual son of ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot</persName>, 
                              donated the book to the monastery of <placeName ref="INS0302SantoSte">Santo Stefano dei Mori</placeName>. 
                              The donation took place in the presence of seven pilgrims, i.e.: rāyǝs <persName ref="PRS11226Yohannes">Yoḥannǝs</persName>, priest <persName ref="PRS11227ZaraLe">Zarʾa Lǝʿul</persName>, 
                              priest <persName ref="PRS11228Yaeqob">Yāʿǝqob</persName>, priest <persName ref="PRS11229TaklaBe">Takla Bǝrhān</persName>, 
                              <persName ref="PRS11230TanseaK">Tanśǝʾa Krǝstos</persName>, <persName ref="PRS11207Ewostateans">spiritual son of ʾabuna ʾEyosṭātewos</persName>, 
                              <persName ref="PRS11231AsrataM">ʿAśrāta Māryām</persName>, <persName ref="PRS11232HouseSam">spiritual son of  ʾabuna Sāmuʾel of Wāldǝbbā</persName>.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The shelfmark <q xml:lang="la">"Vat. | 5 | Aethiop."</q> is written on the front cover, together with the coat of arms of pope <persName ref="PRS7893PiusIX"/>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>"<q xml:lang="it">Tratta della conuersione di S. Pietro sorsa ex Actis Apostolor<supplied>um</supplied></q>" is written on f. <locus target="#Ir"/> by <persName ref="PRS11238Contelori">Felice Contelori</persName>. The note is erased. 
                              Other notes are written in a later hand (<date>17th century</date>): "<quote>10</quote>" (previous shelfmark of the manuscript, then erased); 
                              "<quote xml:lang="la">Epistola Petri. 1. f. 1 | 2 da f. 11 | Epistola s. Iohannis. 1. f. 17 | 2<hi rend="apices">a</hi>. f. 27. | Epistola Iudae. f. 39. | Epistola ad Ebraeos. f. 41. | N° 5</quote>". 
                              The shelfmark "<quote>5. Aethiop.</quote>" is also written on the same leaf in a <date>18th-century</date>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>"<q xml:lang="la">S. Io Chrysostomus</q>" is written in a <date>16th-century</date> hand and erased.</desc>
                              <locus target="#17r"/>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>Doodles on ff. <locus from="62" to="65r"/> and on ff. <locus target="#66r #68v #69v"/>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>Corrections, additions and the chapter numbers according to the Latin Vulgata have been inserted on the left margin of many leaves by <persName ref="PRS9286Tasfase">Tasfā Ṣǝyon</persName>. 
                              The same scholar also numbered the pages containing the text to be printed in his edition of the New Testament: <bibl><ptr target="bm:Petrus1548Test"/></bibl></desc>
                        </item>
                        </list>
